President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring April 2019 as National Child Abuse Prevention Month. In the proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of all Americans working together to protect children from abuse and neglect. The proclamation highlights the negative effects of abuse on children's development and well-being, including increased risk of depression, substance abuse, and future violence. President Trump also mentions the need for strong families, raising awareness, and prevention-based approaches to child welfare. He acknowledges the role of the entire community, including parents, friends, neighbors, educators, and faith leaders, in promoting the well-being of children. The proclamation expresses gratitude towards foster and adoptive parents, as well as professionals, volunteers, and organizations dedicated to protecting at-risk children. President Trump calls upon all Americans to invest in the lives of children, be aware of their safety and well-being, and support efforts that promote their development.